<document>

  <properties>
    <title>Quality control with FastQC step</title>
    <author email="jourdren@biologie.ens.fr">Laurent Jourdren</author>
  </properties>



  <body>

    <section name="Quality control with FastQC step">

      <p>This step allow to run <a href="http://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/fastqc/">FastQC v0.11.2</a> 
      		on fastq or sam files to generate a report html.</p>

      <ul>
         <li><b>Internal name</b>: fastqc</li>
         <li><b>Available</b>: Local only</li>

         <br/>
         <li><b>Input ports</b>:
           <ul>
             <li><b>reads</b>: two available 
             	<ul><li>reads in FASTQ format (format: reads_fastq)</li>
             		<li>alignments in SAM format (format: mapper_results_sam)</li>
             	</ul>
             </li>
           </ul>
         </li>

         <br/>
         <li><b>Output port</b>:
           <ul>
             <li><b>output</b>: report HTML format (format: report_html)</li>
           </ul>
         </li>
         <br/>
         
         <li><b>Optional parameters</b>:</li>
           <table>
                <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th><th>Default value</th></tr>
            	<tr><td>input.format</td><td>string</td><td>Define the input format file, it can be fastq or sam. It is different of sam, fastq is used.</td><td>fastq</td></tr>
           	</table>
           	
         <br/>
         <li><b>Optional FastQC parameters</b>:</li>
           <table>
                <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th><th>Default value</th></tr>
            	<tr><td>fastqc.kmer.size</td><td>integer</td><td>Define the length of Kmer to look for in the Kmer content module. Specified Kmer length must be between 2 and 10</td><td>7</td></tr>
  				<tr><td>fastqc.nogroup</td><td>boolean</td><td>Define if it disable grouping of bases for reads >50bp.</td><td>false</td></tr>
           		<tr><td>fastqc.expgroup</td><td>boolean</td><td>Define it should use exponential base groups in graph.</td><td>false</td></tr>
           		<tr><td>fastqc.casava</td><td>boolean</td><td>Define it is format fastq type casava/Illumina.</td><td>false</td></tr>
           		<tr><td>fastqc.nofilter</td><td>boolean</td><td>Define it should filter read on quality, only available for FASTQ with fastqc.casava=true. </td><td>true</td></tr> 
          </table>

      </ul>
    </section>

  </body>

</document>
